    p.description at this point analyzed near to death by me and A, and still i havent figured it all out - which i think may speak to the flaws in all the material : faulkner, murakami, lee. but this story was still interesting, riveting, and this movie was beautifully shot. I loved seeing the light change in the scene outside Jong su's house. Steven yeun was perhaps too creepy / obviously an unfeeling psychopath.

