  div.movie
    p.title Rope
    p.sub Alfred Hitchcock, 1948
    img(data-src='#{path}/rope.png')
    p.date 27 April 2020
    p.description second Hitchcock film in a week in which a doe-eyed Farley Granger has gotten somehow involved with a murder-happy psychopath. I appreciated the weird camera "transitions" (I put this in quotes because these didn't always change scenes) in this one in which we zoom into someone's back. I also noticed how the film was like an Aristotelian play: unity of time, place, and action. The plot is clearly someone's sadistic nightmare of a dinner party...

